<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Robot Coupe service</p>
    <h2>The dominant US commercial cutter mixer brand, serviced with brush-motor expertise.</h2>
    <p>Robot Coupe R-series cutter mixers dominate the US commercial food processor market. Restaurant prep lines, deli salad production, butcher shop sausage seasoning, ice cream base preparation, hummus and dip operations, and ready-to-eat food assembly all depend on R-series reliability. Robot Coupe is part of SEB Group (Société d'Emboutissage de Bourgogne, French multinational); SEB Group also owns Tefal, Krups, Rowenta, and All-Clad.</p>
    <p>We service the full R-series across all five SoCal counties. <strong>R2</strong> (2.5 quart, smallest, mid-volume prep kitchens). <strong>R4</strong> (4.5 quart, deli salad and sandwich prep). <strong>R8</strong> (8 quart, full-service restaurant workhorse). <strong>R10</strong> (10 quart, high-volume prep operations). <strong>R15</strong> (15 quart, institutional). <strong>R30</strong> (30 quart, floor model for large catering and central kitchen operations).</p>
    <p>Service scope: NSF-listed OEM S-blade sharpening and replacement, brushed motor brush service (Robot Coupe motors are brushed, year 6 to 10 typical brush life), safety interlock service, bowl latch service, drive coupling, motor replacement, pulse switch. NSF-listed OEM Robot Coupe parts only for Health Department compliance.</p>
    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS #A49573 license. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. <a href="/credentials/licensed/">License verifiable.</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">R-Series lineup</p>
    <h2>The Robot Coupe R-series family by capacity.</h2>
    <p class="lead">All R-series share the same brushed motor architecture and S-blade primary cutting tool. Capacity scales linearly; motor wattage and bowl design scale with capacity.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">R2 (2.5 quart, mid-volume prep)</h3>
    <p>Smallest R-series. Common in mid-volume prep kitchens, sandwich shops, and operations where bench space is constrained. Same brushed motor architecture as larger R-series with smaller motor wattage.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">R4 (4.5 quart, deli workhorse)</h3>
    <p>Deli salad and sandwich prep standard. Common in fast-casual chains and full-service deli operations. Slightly larger motor than R2 with same brush block design.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">R8 (8 quart, full-service workhorse)</h3>
    <p>The most common R-series in LA full-service restaurants. Handles standard prep volumes for full menu operations. Larger brush set than R2/R4 with longer typical brush life.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">R10 (10 quart, high-volume prep)</h3>
    <p>High-volume prep operations: large salad programs, dip/spread production, ice cream base preparation. Larger motor with thermal protection threshold appropriate for continuous-cycle operation.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">R15 (15 quart, institutional)</h3>
    <p>School cafeterias, hospital food service, university dining. Bowl size and motor scale require thoughtful dispatch logistics for service work.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">R30 (30 quart floor model)</h3>
    <p>Large catering operations, central kitchen production, wholesale prep. Floor-mounted with industrial-grade brushed motor and large-bowl architecture. Service work requires forklift access for major component swaps on some installations.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2>Top Robot Coupe service items in our 5-county territory.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>S-blade sharpening or replacement.</strong> Routine maintenance every 6 to 18 months depending on usage. Sharpening (when viable) $120 to $180; NSF-listed OEM blade replacement $180 to $360.</li>
      <li><strong>Safety interlock failure.</strong> Year 5 to 9 typical. Lid must be properly seated for motor to run; failed interlock prevents start. $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Motor brush wear.</strong> Robot Coupe motors are brushed; year 6 to 10 typical brush life. Symptom: motor runs erratically, sparking visible at brush block. $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Bowl latch wear.</strong> Lid latches loose, lid won't seat properly. $140 to $260.</li>
      <li><strong>Drive coupling.</strong> Plastic or metal coupling between motor shaft and blade spindle wears or breaks. $200 to $360.</li>
      <li><strong>Motor overload trip.</strong> Operator over-filling the bowl. Reset, reduce batch size, educate operator. No-charge first occurrence.</li>
      <li><strong>Pulse switch service.</strong> Pulse switch contacts wear over time. $140 to $240.</li>
      <li><strong>Motor full replacement.</strong> When brushes are exhausted and commutator is worn beyond service. R8 through R30: $680 to $1,200.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>
    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Restaurant prep kitchen in West Hollywood · Robot Coupe R8 (8 years)</h3>
        <p>Motor running erratically with visible sparking at brush block. Diagnosed: motor brushes worn to base. Replaced brush set plus cleaned commutator. Tested through full prep cycle. Total: $360.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Salad operation in Pasadena · Robot Coupe R10 (5 years)</h3>
        <p>Lid wouldn't seat properly; safety interlock prevented motor start. Bowl latch wear (heavy-cycle use compressed latch over 5 years). Replaced bowl latch plus tested interlock through full cycle. Total: $260.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Ice cream base prep in Beverly Hills · Robot Coupe R15 (10 years)</h3>
        <p>Motor stopped mid-cycle on heavy ice cream base load. Diagnosed: motor overload trip plus brush wear advancing. Reset thermal protection plus replaced brush set preventively (avoiding cascading damage). Educated operator on R15 batch-size limits for ice cream base viscosity. Total: $440.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Catering kitchen in Calabasas · Robot Coupe R30 floor model (12 years)</h3>
        <p>Drive coupling worn; blade spinning slower than motor speed under load. Replaced drive coupling plus inspected motor brush block (still serviceable for another 1 to 2 years). Total: $360.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hummus production in Long Beach · Robot Coupe R10 (7 years)</h3>
        <p>S-blade dulling beyond viable sharpening (third sharpening attempt, blade geometry compromised). Replaced with NSF-listed OEM Robot Coupe S-blade. Total: $360.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Scope</p>
    <h2>What we do for Robot Coupe, and what we don't.</h2>
    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Robot Coupe R-series cutter mixers (R2, R4, R8, R10, R15, R30). NSF-listed OEM S-blade sharpening and replacement, brushed motor brush service, safety interlock service, bowl latch service, drive coupling, motor replacement, pulse switch service.</p>
    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> Robot Coupe vegetable prep attachments standalone service when not paired with cutter mixer (specialty attachment trade); industrial Robot Coupe processing systems for production-line operations (specialty industrial trade); commercial blender service is partial scope (we cover Robot Coupe blender bases but Vitamix Commercial and other blender brands fall on the food processor pillar). New Robot Coupe installation we coordinate but don't perform.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Pricing</p>
    <h2>Robot Coupe R-series repair costs.</h2>
    <p class="lead">Diagnostic is $120 (commercial tier), waived with repair. NSF-listed OEM Robot Coupe parts only for Health Department compliance.</p>
