<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Why operators choose us for Robot Coupe</p>
    <h2>What separates our Robot Coupe service from generalist commercial repair.</h2>
    <ul class="reasons-list">
      <li><strong>Brushed motor expertise.</strong> Robot Coupe motors are brushed; brushed-motor service is service-friendly when techs know the architecture. Many shops misdiagnose worn brushes as full motor failure.</li>
      <li><strong>NSF-listed OEM blades only.</strong> Health Department inspections require NSF-listed blades; aftermarket blades fail inspection regardless of fitment.</li>
      <li><strong>S-blade sharpening discipline.</strong> Robot Coupe S-blades can be sharpened 2 to 3 times during their service life; we sharpen when viable, replace when sharpening would compromise blade geometry.</li>
      <li><strong>R2 through R30 coverage.</strong> All current sizes serviceable with brand-specific knowledge of brush block, drive coupling, and safety interlock variations across capacity tiers.</li>
      <li><strong>SEB Group US distribution access.</strong> 5 to 7 day standard ship for most service items.</li>
      <li><strong>Multi-cause motor diagnosis.</strong> Motor stop mid-cycle: overload trip vs interlock vs brush wear vs commutator damage. We diagnose with multimeter, not by parts swap.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 plus EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410.</strong> Verifiable.</li>
      <li><strong>24/7 phone answering.</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura.</strong></li>
      <li><strong>BBB A+.</strong></li>
    </ul>
